President Obama issued a statement praising Raj Shah for his work as the Administrator of the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID). He commended Shah's efforts to advance the global development agenda, including addressing natural disasters, epidemics, and famine. The President also highlighted Shah's commitment to ending global poverty, promoting food security, health and nutrition, expanding access to energy sources, and supporting political and economic reform in closed societies. Obama expressed gratitude for Shah's leadership and counsel and wished him well in his future endeavors.